<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1969-04-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1969-04-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="246" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d246">
                        <head>246. National Security Study Memorandum 52<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d246fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials,
                                    <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Institutional Files (<gloss target="#t_H1">H</gloss>-Files), Box <gloss target="#t_H1">H</gloss>–150, National Security Study Memoranda, <gloss target="#t_NSSM1">NSSM</gloss> 52. Secret; <gloss target="#t_Exdis1">Exdis</gloss>. Copies were sent to the
                                Director of the Bureau of the Budget and the Chairman of the Joint
                                Chiefs of Staff.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1969-04-26">April 26, 1969</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <list type="to">
                            <head>TO</head>
                            <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                            <item>The Secretary of Defense</item>
                            <item>The Director of Central Intelligence</item>
                        </list>
                        <list type="subject">
                            <head>SUBJECT</head>
                            <item>Military Aid Policy Toward Greece</item>
                        </list>
                        <p>The President has requested a review of our current military aid policy
                            toward Greece.</p>
                        <p>The President has directed that a study be prepared by the <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Interdepartmental Group for the Near
                            East which presents arguments pro and con on the resumption of full
                            military assistance.</p>
                        <p>This study should include an assessment of the present political
                            situation in Greece as it affects <gloss target="#t_US1">U.S.</gloss>
                            interests.</p>
                        <p>This study should be forwarded to the Review Group by May 16.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">
                                    <hi rend="strong">Henry A. Kissinger</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>